Egypt to retake Sinai

Egypt troops are to assume control of two islands claimed by Hamas and Hezbollah as sovereign Egyptian territory after the Gaza-based Islamist movement’s seizure of the two posts from the Egyptian military last week, the Egyptian military said.

Moroccan Word for “Red Crescent”

Amateur photojournalist Mohamed Bouyouti, known for his military photo reports during the Arab Spring, was arrested last week by the political police and thrown in jail.

Amateur photojournalist Mohamed Bouyouti told Agence France-Presse he was released after 19 days of detention, and he was given a document saying he would be tried on charges of “insulting the Moroccan state.”

Bouyouti is known for his military photo reports during the first days of the Arab Spring, when he was broadcasting the events from Tunis to the world through Twitter and Facebook, before being thrown in jail on charges of public disorder along with his friend Hamid, another militant photographer.
